            <h3 data-uuid="cb13f421b48747209e6ca7970bd5512d">Part 2: Write an
                Argument</h3>
            <h6 data-uuid="d60382f4ae2c4fd49af9e441c515a5ee">Historical Context</h6>
            <p data-uuid="e59c20ce1ac94af5b6a044f925495699">The
                earliest beginnings of the nation resulted from the contributions of many
                culturesâ€”Native American, African, and European. When the English colonists
                declared independence, they established a new government rooted in democratic
                ideals. In time, the nation grew, expanded westward, and regional ways of life
                developed. Still, the nation failed to resolve the issue of slavery.
                Ultimately, this failure would lead to civil war.</p>
            <h6 data-uuid="f676c4bdaac840f3863d28dbaf9cd4bb">Task</h6>
            <p data-uuid="96dfbfcc93094ea3994004b887b77489">In
                the years leading up to the Civil War, Americans were both united and divided
                by conflict. How can conflict both unite and divide a nation? Write an
                analytical essay in response to this question.</p>
            <p data-uuid="04194a40844f41fcbc0e91cd331c151d">Complete the
                following steps as you plan and compose your essay.</p>
            <ol data-uuid="5f9fbd7332cf4638b78776d4b56e9913">
                <li data-uuid="092f3953a6c44c03ae2e333d0f01ab84">
                    Review your notes and
                    sources before you start writing.&#160;</li>
                <li data-uuid="d72a516a21514b91b2facf44e16011b3">
                    Use at least <i>three</i> of the sources in Part 1, and
                    develop the topic with relevant, well-chosen text or visual evidence from the
                    documents.</li>
                <li data-uuid="a6212b0f83324b02a275627bc1d774ac">
                    Cite specific text or
                    visual evidence from each of the sources in your response.</li>
                <li data-uuid="9d7f53152127475590c0744113eef67e">
                    Plan your essay so
                    that it includes an introduction, several body paragraphs, and a concluding
                    paragraph.</li>
                <li data-uuid="038118b24e8b4b4ea62fadd9421b63b1">Use clear and relevant
                    details to support your analysis.</li>
                <li data-uuid="9b7ed62128e14a288846fdee554cb70e">Write a conclusion
                    that sums up your ideas and supports the information you present.&#160;</li>
            </ol>
        </section>
